  "text": "The MI is a 24-item self-completion questionnaire to assess psychiatric morbidity in general population surveys [CITATION_1] 14] . Scores were dichotomised: those scoring 5 or less being categorised as ''no malaise'' (76.6%, 8,632) and those scoring above 5 ''malaise present'' (23.4%, 2,639). Rodgers [CITATION_2] demonstrated a sensitivity and specificity of 0.73 and 0.81 for case-level depression using this cutoff point. Confounding factors considered",
